This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on distributed training of deep neural networks using TensorFlow and CUDA-aware MPI. It also involves performance characterization and design analysis of distributed TensorFlow, which is a key aspect of distributed computing. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it deals with deep learning and training of neural networks. 

Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category as deep learning is widely used in computer vision applications. 

Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with training of neural networks. 

Finally, Scientific Computing (cs.SC) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves performance optimization and analysis, which is a key aspect of scientific computing.
